SUMMARY:California Duck Days
DESCRIPTION:Date: Saturday\, April 25\, 2026 in Davis \nTime: 9:00 AM – 3:00 PM \nLocation: Yolo Bypass Wildlife Area  Headquarters\, 45211 County Road 32B (East Chiles Road) Davis\, CA 95618 \nEntry fee: $25/Car \nLEARN MORE: https://yolobasin.org/california-duck-days/ \nCalifornia Duck Days 2026 is Yolo Basin Foundation’s largest family-oriented\, community based outdoor festival of the year. Join in on the fun on Saturday\, April 25 by participating in our various interactive activities which include wetland themed arts and crafts\, live animals\, live music\, and much more! Click the link above to learn more. We cannot wait to see you there!
URL:https://visitdavis.org/event/california-duck-days/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visitdavis.org/wp-content/uploads/DD-2026-Flyer-ENG-Landscape-3_page-0001-1-1-lNJfCV.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Yolo Basin Foundation":MAILTO:cquirk@yolobasin.org
END:VEVENT
